name: Beetlejuice
summary: The long-awaited sequel to the classic supernatural comedy "Beetlejuice" is teased in a new trailer. The trailer features the return of Michael Keaton as the titular mischievous ghost, alongside newcomer Jenna Ortega as Lydia Deetz. The sequel, titled "Beetlejuice Beetlejuice," promises to stay true to the original's quirky and macabre tone, with glimpses of practical effects and over-the-top set design. The trailer hints at the plot, revealing Lydia's encounter with a new family that unwittingly summons Beetlejuice upon their house. The trailer also confirms the return of Winona Ryder as Lydia's mother and Catherine O'Hara as a mysterious character, while hinting at a cameo from an undisclosed "beloved Tim Burton actor." With its eye-catching aesthetics and the promise of Keaton's signature performance, "Beetlejuice Beetlejuice" seems poised to reclaim the cult status of its predecessor.

summary: Former Baltimore City State's Attorney Marilyn Mosby has been sentenced to one year of home confinement and ordered to forfeit her Florida vacation home for mortgage fraud and perjury convictions. Despite a request for a pardon ahead of sentencing, Mosby was spared a prison sentence.

name: Carlo Acutis
summary: Pope Francis has recognized a second miracle attributed to the late Italian teenager Carlo Acutis, clearing the path for his canonization as the Catholic Church's first "millennial" saint. Acutis, who died of leukemia in 2006 at the age of 15, is known for his devout faith, his love of the Eucharist, and his skills in computer programming. He has been widely hailed as a role model for young people and has been the subject of numerous articles, books, and even a film. Acutis's canonization process began in 2013, and he was declared "Blessed" in 2020. The latest miracle recognized by the Pope involves the unexplained healing of a Brazilian boy from a rare pancreatic ailment. Acutis's canonization is expected to take place in Rome in the coming months.

name: Memorial Day meaning
summary: Memorial Day, observed on the last Monday in May each year, is a federal holiday honoring military members who died while serving their country. This year, Memorial Day falls on May 27th, 2024. The holiday serves as a time for remembrance, reflection, and appreciation for the sacrifices made by these fallen heroes. Veterans, military members, and their families participate in various ceremonies and events to pay tribute to their comrades and loved ones who have passed. The holiday also sparks discussions about its meaning and significance, with some advocating for changes to federal holidays, including Memorial Day, to better reflect the sacrifices of those who have defended the nation.
